<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2365] C# decodes too many binary bytes from JSON</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2365</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the length of a certain binary data block is not a multiple of 3 (e.g. 16384 bytes), the JSON decoder returns a byte[] array with the length of the next multiple of 3 (e.g. 16386 bytes), because possible &lt;a href=&quot;http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4648#section-4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;base64 fill bytes&lt;/a&gt;  contained in the input data are not handled correctly during the decoding process. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
